snippet.textDisplay: The goal is to buy the more expensive parts that are crucial to the build, and cheap out where you can.. You dont need a $2,000 Titanium exhaust, and you can make just as much power, and sound just as good with cheap stainless from china with proper welds. Same with rims. If you are not tracking your car hard, you dont need $500 a piece rims. For me, I will splurge on top parts on for the crucial things.. Engine compnents and suspension. I will usually cheap out on exhaust pieces, manifold pieces, and just redo the welds myself and save myself hundreds and hundreds of dollars. The only time it is worth going all top of the line parts is for track builds that take heavy beatings and that need the quality control and better manufacturing. But for daily cars, you can get away with cheaping out alot as long as you do your research and get parts that arent complete shit.
